notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

pipeline_summary.name: Content Moderation Pipeline
pipeline_summary.description: Scans usergenerated content for toxicity, branches based on a 0.7 threshold, and merges results for audit logging.

components.name: Extract User Content CSV
components.description: Reads the CSV file containing usergenerated content and emits metadata such as total item count and file path via XCom.

connections.purpose: Read CSV file from local disk

components.name: Evaluate Toxicity and Branch
components.description: Computes a mock toxicity score for the extracted content and decides which downstream path to follow based on a 0.7 threshold.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful extraction of user content

components.name: Remove Toxic Content and Flag Users
components.description: When toxicity exceeds the threshold, deletes the offending content from the platform and flags the associated user accounts for review.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only when the toxicity branch decision selects the hightoxicity path

connections.purpose: Interact with the platform's content management system

components.name: Publish Safe Content
components.description: When toxicity is at or below the threshold, publishes the safe usergenerated content to the platform for visibility.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered only when the toxicity branch decision selects the lowtoxicity path

components.name: Create Consolidated Audit Log
components.description: Aggregates outcomes from both the removal/flag and publishing branches and writes a unified audit log entry.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after whichever branch (removal or publishing) completes, consolidating their results

description.default: Scans usergenerated content for toxicity, branches based on a 0.7 threshold, and merges results for audit logging.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

csv_path.description: Path to the CSV file containing usergenerated content

toxicity_threshold.description: Score threshold that determines branching (high toxicity > threshold)

provide_context.description: Enable XCom context passing from both upstream branches

sources: Usergenerated content CSV file located at /data/user_content.csv
sinks: Content Management System for removal of toxic content
Publishing System for publishing safe content
Audit Logging System for recording processing outcomes
intermediate_datasets: XCom metadata containing total_items and file_path
